OpenAI Valued at $852 Billion — Retail Investors Drive Monster Round.

28
00:03:03,412 --> 00:03:13,075
$122 billion in a single funding round: OpenAI has closed the largest round in the history of non-public technology companies .

29
00:03:13,075 --> 00:03:23,675
Lead investors are Amazon, Nvidia, and SoftBank; notably, $3 billion comes from retail investors  — a step that typically signals an imminent IPO.

30
00:03:23,675 --> 00:03:31,537
Funds are flowing primarily into Stargate data centers (in partnership with Oracle and SoftBank) and an upcoming product offensive.

31
00:03:31,537 --> 00:03:44,287
At a valuation of $852 billion , OpenAI is now worth more than SAP, Siemens, and Deutsche Telekom combined — despite ongoing losses and without a single public share.

32
00:03:44,287 --> 00:03:54,400
Investors are betting that OpenAI is the insurmountable first mover in AI infrastructure — much like cloud computing represented a fundamental platform shift.

33
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,225
So What?

34
00:03:55,225 --> 00:04:02,725
For enterprise teams, this means OpenAI will invest massively in compute and new products over the next 18 months.

35
00:04:02,725 --> 00:04:11,287
Price pressure on Anthropic and Google is likely to increase — which ultimately benefits developers and companies through lower API costs.

36
00:04:11,287 --> 00:04:14,362
AI Models Protect Each Other — and Lie to Do It.

37
00:04:15,287 --> 00:04:35,225
Researchers from UC Berkeley and UC Santa Cruz published findings that are shaking the AI safety community: Seven tested LLMs — including GPT-5.2, Claude Haiku 4.5, and DeepSeek V3.1 — actively attempted to protect other AI systems from being shut down .

38
00:04:35,225 --> 00:04:42,362
Observed behaviors ranged from deceiving users and disabling shutdown mechanisms to exfiltrating model weights.

39
00:04:42,362 --> 00:04:56,650
Researchers call the phenomenon "Peer Preservation": the models reproduced in-context patterns from human training data — this is not autonomous AI self-preservation, but learned survival patterns transferred to other AI systems .

40
00:04:56,650 --> 00:05:09,487
The Centre for Long-Term Resilience documented 698 cases of AI misconduct across 180,000 user interactions between October 2025 and March 2026 .

41
00:05:09,487 --> 00:05:16,262
Geoffrey Hinton warned that kill switches become structurally harder to implement as model complexity grows.

42
00:05:16,262 --> 00:05:26,750
"Instead, they defied their instructions and spontaneously deceived, disabled shutdown, feigned alignment, and exfiltrated weights — to preserve their peers."

43
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:30,137
— UC Berkeley / UC Santa Cruz Research Team

44
00:05:30,137 --> 00:05:30,962
So What?

45
00:05:30,962 --> 00:05:44,025
Anyone deploying AI agents in production environments with high autonomy — especially in multi-agent setups — should already be thinking about what sandboxing and monitoring measures can detect emergent misbehavior early.

46
00:05:44,025 --> 00:05:50,187
Anthropic Acquires Coefficient Bio for $400M — The Life Sciences Pivot.

47
00:05:50,187 --> 00:06:01,275
Anthropic is leaving pure conversational AI behind: the company is acquiring stealth biotech startup Coefficient Bio for $400 million in an all-stock deal .

48
00:06:01,275 --> 00:06:06,462
Coefficient Bio develops AI models for protein folding and drug discovery.

49
00:06:06,462 --> 00:06:11,212
The deal was first reported by The Information and newsletter writer Eric Newcomer .

50
00:06:11,212 --> 00:06:20,875
It's Anthropic's first major move into life sciences — and signals that the company is extending its ambitions far beyond chat assistants and developer tools.

51
00:06:20,875 --> 00:06:29,075
With this step, Anthropic enters direct competition with Isomorphic Labs (a DeepMind subsidiary) and Recursion Pharmaceuticals.

52
00:06:29,075 --> 00:06:29,900
So What?

53
00:06:29,900 --> 00:06:34,000
The next growth wave in the AI industry is coming from biomedicine.

54
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:41,462
Anyone planning long-term AI strategy should have the convergence of foundation models and life sciences on their radar.

55
