60
00:07:26,887 --> 00:07:28,012
Tool of the Week.

61
00:07:28,012 --> 00:07:31,937
Mistral Spaces — CLI for Humans and AI Agents.

62
00:07:31,937 --> 00:07:43,537
Mistral AI has released "Spaces"  — a command-line interface built from the ground up for use by AI agents while simultaneously being more ergonomic for human developers than classic CLIs.

63
00:07:43,537 --> 00:07:54,125
The central design principle: "Every prompt is a flag in disguise"  — every interactive input that would normally wait on stdin gets a flag equivalent for headless operation.

64
00:07:54,125 --> 00:08:04,075
Five core principles drive Spaces: explicit state, structured output, no blocking stdin prompts, introspective plugins, and context files .

65
00:08:04,075 --> 00:08:13,975
In a demo, an agent completed the full journey from prompt to live deployment — including Docker, container registry, and GitHub Actions — in under 10 minutes .

66
00:08:13,975 --> 00:08:19,800
The philosophy behind it: "Designing for agents forced us to build better tools for everyone" .

67
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:33,075
Particularly useful for teams looking to automate CI/CD pipelines with AI agents: Spaces delivers a reference design for agent-friendly CLIs that is immediately more usable even without AI.

68
00:08:33,075 --> 00:08:34,700
Try Mistral Spaces

69
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:35,850
Fail of the Week.

70
00:08:35,850 --> 00:08:41,675
"~$1 Million Daily Loss (Estimated) — and Barely Anyone Was Using It Anymore"

71
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,612
OpenAI is shutting down Sora.

72
00:08:44,612 --> 00:08:55,475
On April 26, 2026, access to the video generation model — once considered OpenAI's most hyped product since ChatGPT — comes to an end .

73
00:08:55,475 --> 00:09:05,637
According to industry reports, daily losses were around $1 million — an estimate OpenAI has not officially confirmed  — alongside declining usage.

74
00:09:05,637 --> 00:09:14,137
Resources are being redirected into World Models and Robotics — areas where OpenAI sees strategically more important positions.

75
00:09:14,137 --> 00:09:21,687
Root Cause: Sora was technically an impressive showcase — the quality of generated videos had set benchmarks at launch.

76
00:09:21,687 --> 00:09:25,012
Economically, however, the product never scaled.

77
00:09:25,012 --> 00:09:34,825
Production costs for high-quality video generation remained prohibitively high while competitors like Runway and Pika Labs aggressively caught up with cheaper alternatives.

78
00:09:34,825 --> 00:09:41,250
The product fell into a valley between too expensive for the mass market and too weak for professional production.

79
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:46,525
What We Learn: Technical performance and economic viability are two different things.

80
00:09:46,525 --> 00:09:53,537
Anyone planning AI products should analyze the cost-per-output curve just as rigorously as technical benchmarks.

